benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/xml - Retrieve the full catalog as XML

covered: Valid Request: The tests cover retrieval of latest catalog (TC01), date-based retrieval (TC02), account-based retrieval (TC03), and combined date+account retrieval (TC04) with 200 OK and XML content.
Empty/No Data Handling: Scenarios for no catalog (TC05) and empty catalog (TC15) validate behavior when data is absent or catalog is empty.
Query Parameters Coverage: Tests exercise valid and invalid query parameters including requestedDate and accountId (TC02, TC04, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC16) and ensure appropriate responses.
Authorization and Security: Tests cover unauthorized (TC10) and forbidden (TC11) access, along with input validation against injection (TC13).

Resilience and performance: Scenarios cover service unavailability (TC12), transient network recovery (TC14), very large catalogs (TC17) and concurrent requests (TC18), peak load performance (TC21), and timeouts (TC22).
Regression and compatibility: Tests include regression (TC19) and backward compatibility (TC20) checks, as well as accessibility checks (TC23, TC24).
gaps: Pagination: No explicit pagination tests for large catalogs or paging through results.
Caching Behavior: No tests verifying caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) or caching semantics (e.g., 304 Not Modified).
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or 429 responses under high request rates.
Internal Server Error Path: No tests simulating a 500 Internal Server Error (e.g., DB failure).
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to verify page sizing and navigation across multiple pages for large catalogs.
Add caching-related tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control headers and 304 Not Modified behavior.
Add rate-limiting tests to ensure 429 responses under burst/high load scenarios.
Add tests that simulate 500 Internal Server Error to verify server-side failure handling and error messaging.
